5:
See, these poor people go out to their work\q like wild donkeys in the wilderness, looking carefully for food;
\q perhaps the Arabah will provide them food for their children.
\q

14:
Before daylight the murderer rises \q and he kills poor and needy people;
\q in the night he is like a thief.


\q

16:
In the darkness wicked people dig into houses;\q but they shut themselves up in the daytime;
\q they do not care for the light.
\q

18:
Swiftly they pass away, however, like foam on the surface of the waters;\q their portion of the land is cursed;
\q no one goes to work in their vineyards.
\q

20:
The womb that bore him will forget him;\q the worm will feed sweetly on him;
\q he will be remembered no more;
\q in this way, wickedness will be broken like a tree.
\q

24:
These people are exalted; still, in only a little while, they will be gone;\q indeed, they will be brought low; they will be gathered up like all the others;
\q they will be cut off like the tops of ears of grain.
\q
